main event: Pieces of foil identified as radar chaff were found on the ground near woods in Willis, Virginia during the night.
interesting points: The sighting involved multiple pieces of foil found on the ground,The objects were sent to ATIC for analysis,The foil strips were confirmed to be radar chaff used for military purposes,There was a notable correspondence from Major Lawrence J. Tacker regarding the sighting,The sighting is linked to an incident reported by a civilian concerning debris near their home.
witness description: a civilian reporting fallen radar chaff
